place_info.title: Roastery Coffee House
place_info.address: 8 2, 418, 287/12, Road No. 14, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500034, India

reviews.snippet:
This is a great place for people looking to have a well rounded meal along with a cup of hot speciality coffee. The food was great and the service was excellent.
The restaurant had great attention to detail. They had water spray for the outdoor seating to ensure the heat does not cause the people who opt for it to have a less than ideal experience.
They had a good spread both on the menu and also with respect to the speciality coffees. I would recommend this as a must visit place if you are in and around Banjara hills.

reviews.snippet:
I really love your café. Everything is just perfect—especially your coffee, which I truly believe is the best in town. All your staff members are incredibly courteous and well-informed about the menu. What impressed me most is how well they understand the preferences and needs of the customers.

As a pet parent, I was especially touched by how warmly my dog was welcomed. The complimentary dog food is a wonderful idea, and the way your staff treats her—with the same care and attention as any guest—is heartwarming. I couldn’t be happier. Thank you for creating such a thoughtful and inclusive space.

reviews.snippet: The cranberry coffee just blew my mind. I absolutely loved it and the taste lingers in the mouth long after you’ve had it. We also had the chicken peri peri flat bread pizza and burnt cheese cake with chocolate sauce. Everything was top quality, fresh and delicious. And what made our dining experience better was the pleasant service by Ms. Fiza. She takes care of every customer like her own guest and is mindful of their requirements. Ms. Fiza makes dining at Roastery a thoroughly enjoyable experience.

reviews.snippet: The ambience was really simple inside. Didn't like the plain walls. Service was good and food came out quick. Tried the Spinach Corn sandwich and BBQ chicken burger. Both of the portions were very good and the filling was generous.

reviews.snippet: Atmosphere is the best part of this place. Very chill, and especially at night the lights and plants are so pretty outside. We just came for coffee and dessert. The coffee was alright. If you’re into the more snooty, high end coffee it’s probably great. For me a little overdone, but I do like the way they serve it in different glasses. For dessert we tried carrot cake and the burnt cheesecake. The carrot cake was not carrot cake. It was still good though. It’s just not proper carrot cake. The cheesecake was quite different. It actually tasted more like the Mexican sweet flan, but it was good. The service is very slow, but that’s understandable as they are very busy. Overall a nice place to chill.

Decent prices, great place for couples and even families of that matter. Both indoor and outdoor seating are available and if you want to sit outdoors, i would recommend either morning time or past 4pm in the evening.

Although for outdoor seating there's water sprinkles that dispense a spray of water to keep the place cool. It's basically tiny droplets

reviews.snippet:
Roastery is an easy recommendation be it for someone who likes coffee or someone who just likes to experience good food in a cosy place with a lovely ambience.

Just be aware that it's almost always crowded here and you may have to wait a little depending on what time of the day you decide to visit.

The few times I visited the service was really good and timely, everything that i ordered was yummy and totally worth it.

reviews.snippet: I suppose there is always rush in the evenings. I visited on a Friday evening and there was a wait time. There is no music on the premises, and services were rather delayed. I ordered red pasta and requested penne, but he brought me spaghetti. However, when I requested, he replaced it. The taste was not to my satisfaction, but I also got a cappuccino, which was wonderful. Overall, this was not my preferred option because the crowd was too loud and there was no relaxing music to help me relax. Perhaps I went at the incorrect time.

reviews.snippet:
A must visit for food lovers and ambiance seekers !!
The food was absolutely delicious, with each dish perfectly seasoned and beautifully presented
What really set this restaurant apart, though, was the ambiance. The interior was thoughtfully designed with a perfect blend of modern elegance and cozy charm. Soft lighting, comfortable seating, and tasteful decor created a warm and inviting atmosphere that made the meal even more enjoyable. Whether you're looking for a casual dinner or a special evening out, this place has the perfect vibe.

reviews.snippet:
Review for Roastery Coffee House

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️☆ (4/5)

Roastery Coffee House was a lovely experience. The setting is beautiful, especially the outdoor area, which adds to the charm. We had breakfast—the omelettes were lovely, and the granola bowl was delicious.

The staff was attentive and went out of their way to make us comfortable, which was a big plus. However, it would have been nice if they had a designated smoking section, as that would have made me more likely to return.

Coffee-wise, the cappuccino was good, but the pour-over was just ordinary. That said, the ambiance, set in an old house with multiple levels, makes it a great place to visit. Worth checking out!

reviews.snippet:
We tried their sweet nitro cold brew, zucchini fries and chocolate cheese cake. The sweet nitro cold brew is good.. not better than their cranberry cold coffee.. but it is good.
The zucchini fries were good as well... The quantity is satisfactory. The chocolate cheese cake was not at all worth the price.

The service was so slow and we've been given wrong orders twice.
The ambience is top notch.. very pretty.

reviews.snippet:
The cafe was good in general but nothing was amazing or overwhelming!

Their service was great, we got our food on time! The ambiance was good too, however the outdoor seating can go for a toss if it starts raining! They could have a retractable roof of sorts for the outdoor seating area to avoid this.

The coffess were average (We ordered 2) at best buy why I still gave food a solid 4 rating is because the pasta was amazing!

What Seemed Missing?
I would like to have more options in their coffee menu. As someone who loves a plane and simple iced coffee with no sugar, I left the place wanting more.

Plus they have valet parking service too, which is a definite plus majorly because the locality can be at times confusing and doesn't have a lot of parking space available.

reviews.snippet: This place is a chill spot for a coffee fix, with some unique options on the menu! Tried the Cranberry Coffee - a Roastery invention & a trademark creation, Americano, and Nutella Blend – all were great, but the Cranberry Coffee really stood out. The food didn’t disappoint either; the Cheese Balls and Potato Cutlet Sandwich were awesome. The whole vibe is super aesthetic, and they’ve got some great coffee beans to choose from. I even snagged a pouch of beans ground to my pour-over preference. Definitely worth a visit!

reviews.snippet:
Been here on a festival and it has got a very good vibe. We had waited for nearly 50 mins to get a table. Service from the staff was great. Coming to the food we have tried:
Mushroom and Cheese Bruschetta and it was awesome.
Peri Peri chicken pizza was decent.
We had Chicken Kheema Lasagna and it was disappointing. The chicken kheema was so hard and everyone who has tried this at our table had our stomach upset the next day. Rest of all the food items were good.

reviews.snippet:
The atmosphere and setting of the coffee house has been wonderfully done.
Loved the light decor on the trees and walk way.
I had the burnt cheese cake with milk mocha(diary version), along with fish and chips.
Would recommend the same, I also loved the  diary free option(oats milk) that was on the menu.
Pleased and highly appreciative of the service provided, they are readily available and provide good suggestions. The service was the highlight for me.
Thank you!
